    <summaries>
      <summary>
        <versionCode>00</versionCode>
        <actionDate>2003-08-01</actionDate>
        <actionDesc>Introduced in Senate</actionDesc>
        <updateDate>2003-10-16T19:23:58Z</updateDate>
        <text><![CDATA[ <p>Religious Liberties Restoration Act - States that the following powers are reserved to the States or their political subdivisions on property owned or administered by them: (1) to display the Ten Commandments; (2) to recite the Pledge of Allegiance as: "I pledge allegiance to the Flag of the United States of America, and to the Republic for which it stands, one Nation under God, indivisible, with liberty and justice for all "; and (3) to recite the national motto as "In God we trust". </p> <p>States that such powers are excepted from the jurisdiction of Federal courts inferior to the Supreme Court. </p>]]></text>
      </summary>
